    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Term that was appropriated first by the Surrealists from physiology and psychiatry, and later applied to spontaneous writing, drawing, and painting. Automatism in the visual arts includes techniques in other movements as well, such as Abstract Expressionism and others, referring generally to manual creation techniques involving chance or psychological experiences.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Term die als eerste door de surrealisten werd gebruikt, op basis van dit begrip in de fysiologie en de psychiatrie, en die later werd toegepast op spontaan schrijven, tekenen en schilderen. Automatisme in de beeldende kunst kan ook betrekking hebben op technieken in andere bewegingen, zoals abstract expressionisme, waarbij in het algemeen verwezen wordt naar technieken waarmee met de hand dingen worden gemaakt en waarbij het toeval of psychologische ervaringen een rol spelen.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Termo que foi apropriado primeiro pelos surrealistas da fisiologia e da psiquiatria, e depois aplicado à escrita, desenho e pintura espontâneos. O automatismo nas artes visuais inclui técnicas também em outros movimentos, como o expressionismo abstrato e outros, referindo-se geralmente a técnicas de criação manual envolvendo o acaso ou experiências psicológicas.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Portuguese</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
